            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "That is honestly very good, but incomplete. \n\nThe document is about deployment with nginx+uwsgi, yet there's no mention of `uwsgi_intercept_errors` and not a word about working out production configuration issues. Some paths might be off, some permissions might need to be set, but the only clue you'll get following this document is a line like this in uwsgi log `[pid: 3528|app: 0|req: 1/1] 1.2.3.4 () {40 vars in 691 bytes} [Thu Nov 10 15:35:06 2011] GET /free-beta/ => generated 291 bytes in 25 msecs (HTTP/1.1 500) 2 headers in 84 bytes (1 switches on core 0)`\n\nCan you see it? The **500** right near the end of the line? \n\nHow does one get something more verbose to show up in logs? Not a word of that in the doc.\n"
        },
