            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Your link is about error handling within Flask. What I meant was that the doc about uwsgi could do with a mentioning of `uwsgi_intercept_errors on` parameter for nginx in production, and `app.debug = True` to see a python stack trace in uwsgi logs. \n\nAnd I'm not familiar with uwsgi either. That's why I find the Flask doc in that part lacking. \n"
